# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# .dockerignore — tells Docker which files to SKIP when building an image.
#
# When you run "docker build .", Docker sends ALL files in the current
# directory to the Docker daemon (the "build context"). Without this file,
# that includes .git/ (hundreds of MB of history), secrets/, tests/, etc.
#
# This file works exactly like .gitignore but for Docker builds.
# Every pattern listed here is EXCLUDED from the build context.
#
# WHY THIS MATTERS:
#   - .bootstrap-secrets/ and secrets/ contain PASSWORDS. Without this file,
#     they'd be sent to the Docker daemon (even if not COPY'd into the image).
#   - .git/ can be 100+ MB. Skipping it makes builds faster.
#   - tests/ and scripts/ aren't needed in the production image.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Git history — not needed in the Docker image, and can be very large
.git

# GitHub Actions workflows — only used by CI, not by the running app
.github

# Local secrets — NEVER send these to the Docker build context
.bootstrap-secrets
secrets

# Local development files — not needed in production
local
tests
scripts

# Documentation — not needed in the running container
*.md

# Config files — not needed in the image (they're used by CI/scripts, not the app)
.gitignore
.gitleaks.toml
.dockerignore

# Python bytecode — regenerated at runtime
__pycache__
*.pyc

# Python virtual environments
.venv
venv

# macOS metadata
.DS_Store

# Editor settings
.idea
.vscode
